    • checkLocation

      protected void checkLocation()
      Check that the location has been correctly set for this tree. By default, this checks that getLocation() does not return null, but can be overridden for particular classes that do not require location information. Do not check anything about the location. It is possible to use setLocation() on a list, but it is also OK not to set it.
      Overrides:
      checkLocation in class Tree
